1
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:40,840
Young people from all over the globe...

2
00:00:40,850 --> 00:00:42,970
are joining up to fight for the future.

3
00:00:42,980 --> 00:00:45,820
- I'm doing my part. - I'm doing my part.

4
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:49,490
- I'm doing my part. - I'm doing my part too.

5
00:00:51,220 --> 00:00:53,610
They're doing their part, are you?

6
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:56,190
Join the Mobile Infantry and save the world.

7
00:00:56,290 --> 00:00:58,780
Service guarantees citizenship.

8
00:01:02,710 --> 00:01:05,750
The bugs send another meteor our way...

9
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:07,630
but this time we're ready.

10
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:11,170
Planetary defences are better than ever.

11
00:01:15,810 --> 00:01:18,380
Klendathu, source of the bug meteor attacks...

12
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:21,890
orbits a twin star system whose brutal gravitational forces...

13
00:01:21,980 --> 00:01:25,020
produce an unlimited supply of bug meteorites...

14
00:01:25,110 --> 00:01:27,730
in the form of this asteroid belt.

15
00:01:27,820 --> 00:01:30,060
To ensure the safety of our solar system...

16
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:32,650
Klendathu must be eliminated.

17
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:36,910
We break net now and take you live to Klendathu...

18
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,750
where the invasion has begun.

19
00:01:39,830 --> 00:01:43,250
EXQ uplink on two, one. You're on.

20
00:01:43,340 --> 00:01:45,910
- We'vejust landed here on what cap troopers... - Move, move, move!

21
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,080
- are calling Big K, - Come on! Move, move!

22
00:01:48,170 --> 00:01:50,750
- with the 6th Mobile Infantry Division! - Come on!

23
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:54,090
It's an ugly planet, a bug planet!

24
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:56,880
A planet hostile to life as we know it!

25
00:02:00,350 --> 00:02:01,730
Help me!

26
00:02:12,780 --> 00:02:15,570
- Come on! Go, go, go! - Keep moving!

27
00:02:15,660 --> 00:02:17,320
Get out of here now!

28
00:02:26,670 --> 00:02:28,250
Kitten, no!

29
00:02:57,040 --> 00:03:00,990
Rico. Rico.

30
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,150
Rico!

31
00:03:05,030 --> 00:03:06,940
Pay attention.

32
00:03:07,940 --> 00:03:09,760
Sorry, Mr Rasczak.

33
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,810
Let's sum up.

34
00:03:12,070 --> 00:03:15,340
This year we explored the failure of democracy...

35
00:03:15,390 --> 00:03:17,430
- Bad boy. - how the social scientists brought our world...

36
00:03:17,460 --> 00:03:19,130
to the brink of chaos.

37
00:03:19,220 --> 00:03:21,970
We talked about the veterans, how they took control...

38
00:03:22,060 --> 00:03:26,350
and imposed the stability that has lasted for generations since.

39
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,920
You know these facts...

40
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:30,640
but have I taught you anything of value this year?

41
00:03:32,090 --> 00:03:34,470
You. Why are only citizens allowed to vote?

42
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,900
It's a reward

43
00:03:35,990 --> 00:03:39,020
what the Federation gives you for doing Federal Service.

44
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,980
No. No.

45
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:44,580
Something given has no value.

46
00:03:44,660 --> 00:03:47,950
Look, when you vote, you are exercising political authority.

47
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:51,990
You're using force. And force, my friends, is violence,

48
00:03:52,090 --> 00:03:55,920
the supreme authority from which all other authority is derived.

49
00:03:56,010 --> 00:03:59,090
Uh, my mother always said violence never solves anything.

50
00:03:59,180 --> 00:04:00,670
Really?

51
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:04,220
I wonder what the city fathers of Hiroshima would say about that.

52
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:05,600
You.

53
00:04:06,070 --> 00:04:10,100
They probably wouldn't say anything. Hiroshima was destroyed.

54
00:04:10,190 --> 00:04:11,520
Correct.

55
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,770
Naked force has resolved more issues...

56
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:16,400
throughout history than any other factor.

57
00:04:16,410 --> 00:04:19,940
The contrary opinion, that violence never solves anything,

58
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:22,320
is wishful thinking at its worst.

59
00:04:22,410 --> 00:04:25,580
People who forget that always pay.

60
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:29,250
Rico, what's the moral difference, if any...

61
00:04:29,330 --> 00:04:31,290
between a civilian and a citizen?

62
00:04:31,380 --> 00:04:34,410
A citizen accepts personal responsibility for the safety...

63
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:37,460
of the body politic, defending it with his life.

64
00:04:37,580 --> 00:04:41,180
- A civilian does not. - The exact words of the text.

65
00:04:41,350 --> 00:04:44,840
But do you understand it? Do you believe it?

66
00:04:45,650 --> 00:04:49,100
- I don't know. - Of course you don't.

67
00:04:49,130 --> 00:04:51,260
I doubt anyone here would recognize civic virtue...

68
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:53,880
if it reached up and bit you in the ass.

69
00:05:11,250 --> 00:05:13,040
Not here.

70
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:15,330
Come on, let's see if they posted the math final.

71
00:05:15,340 --> 00:05:18,690
- Rico, we gonna take Tesla? - We're gonna kill 'em.

72
00:05:21,510 --> 00:05:24,160
Remember, all graduating seniors must fill out a 710 form.

73
00:05:24,350 --> 00:05:26,760
First thing Fleet Academy looks at is your math scores.

74
00:05:26,790 --> 00:05:28,230
Wish me luck.

75
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:38,380
- Way to go. - Good job.

76
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:40,900
Your turn. Hold on.

77
00:05:40,990 --> 00:05:43,560
I want to talk to Marco. His sister's at Fleet.

78
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,490
- Marco. - Hi, Carmen.

79
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:48,070
- What do you hear about Roxy? - She made pilot.

80
00:05:51,210 --> 00:05:53,700
Thirty-five percent. Very nice.

81
00:05:55,460 --> 00:06:00,120
Look at that. Thirty-five percent, ladies and gentlemen.

82
00:06:00,150 --> 00:06:01,500
Big numbers.

83
00:06:01,590 --> 00:06:03,470
- Carl. - Sorry.

84
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:13,010
So, you haven't done it yet, have you? Don't lie.

85
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:14,810
I'm not in any hurry.

86
00:06:15,910 --> 00:06:18,060
- Others are waiting. - And?

87
00:06:19,130 --> 00:06:21,320
- Did you read her mind? - Don't have to.

88
00:06:21,330 --> 00:06:23,650
It's pretty clear what she wants.

89
00:06:23,690 --> 00:06:26,190
Yeah, but I want Carmen.

90
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:28,400
- Aw, you got it bad. - Bye, Marco.

91
00:06:28,420 --> 00:06:29,870
Hey, don't forget about this afternoon.

92
00:06:29,900 --> 00:06:32,580
He's always late when he walks you home to fish for a kiss.

93
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,420
Get out of here.

94
00:06:34,530 --> 00:06:37,950
- Marco's sister made pilot. - So will you.

95
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:42,170
I mean, imagine flying a half a million tons of starship.

96
00:06:42,180 --> 00:06:43,880
You gotta have nerves of steel.

97
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:46,510
Yeah, you do. Let's see how yours hold up.

98
00:06:46,550 --> 00:06:48,070
You may begin.

99
00:06:58,570 --> 00:07:01,860
Aw, come on, it's just a bug. You better put your goggles on.

100
00:07:01,910 --> 00:07:03,400
"Just a bug."

101
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:07,530
We humans like to think we are nature's finest achievement.

102
00:07:07,620 --> 00:07:09,860
I'm afraid it just isn't true.

103
00:07:09,950 --> 00:07:14,410
This Arkellian sand beetle is superior in many ways.

104
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:19,210
It reproduces in vast numbers, has no ego...

105
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:23,340
has no fear, doesn't now about death...

106
00:07:23,370 --> 00:07:27,290
and so is the perfect selfless member of society.

107
00:07:27,330 --> 00:07:29,880
But humans have created art, mathematics...

108
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:32,590
and interstellar travel.

109
00:07:32,610 --> 00:07:35,690
True. But before you let that go to your head...

110
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:38,100
take the example of the Arachnids...

111
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:41,440
a highly evolved insect society.

112
00:07:41,530 --> 00:07:44,530
By human standards, they are relatively stupid...

113
00:07:44,610 --> 00:07:48,660
but their evolution stretches over millions of years...

114
00:07:49,550 --> 00:07:51,230
- and now... - Here, take this.

115
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:53,740
they can colonize planets...

116
00:07:53,790 --> 00:07:56,750
by hurling their spore into space.

117
00:07:56,830 --> 00:07:59,080
Okay, I think we got it.

118
00:07:59,110 --> 00:08:00,500
That's the heart.

119
00:08:02,170 --> 00:08:04,070
And here's the stomach.

120
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:11,590
Nerves of steel, huh?

121
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:18,590
Don't think about it. Just go on instinct.

122
00:08:18,630 --> 00:08:20,400
Try to visualize it.

123
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:37,790
I see the ace of spades.

124
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:43,030
You know, statistically speaking,

125
00:08:43,060 --> 00:08:45,810
you should have accidentally guessed right by now.

126
00:08:45,890 --> 00:08:50,720
- Try another. - So my psychic abilities are zero and I'm unlucky.

127
00:08:50,810 --> 00:08:52,850
No, luck's not a factor.

128
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:55,810
No one really knows why some people are sensitive and some aren't.

129
00:08:55,900 --> 00:08:59,020
Who knows? Maybe it's a new stage of human evolution.

130
00:08:59,110 --> 00:09:01,950
That's why they do these kind of Federal studies.

131
00:09:02,030 --> 00:09:05,070
What... Cyrano... Oh, shit. Time out.

132
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:06,540
Oh, he just wants some attention.

133
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:08,250
You don't play with him any more.

134
00:09:08,580 --> 00:09:09,730
Cyrano.

135
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:14,750
Go bug Mom, Cyrano.

136
00:09:24,180 --> 00:09:26,300
How do you make him do that?

137
00:09:26,470 --> 00:09:29,890
Oh, I gave him the impression there's a grub crawling up my mom's leg.

138
00:09:29,950 --> 00:09:31,740
He's on a mission to go eat it.

139
00:09:31,810 --> 00:09:37,440
Ow! Oh! Get out! Get off my leg! Oh! Carl!

140
00:09:39,460 --> 00:09:42,080
I sure hope you don't do anything like that to me.

141
00:09:42,170 --> 00:09:46,700
Don't be afraid. Can't do human. Yet.

142
00:09:46,790 --> 00:09:48,470
Yeah!

143
00:09:54,290 --> 00:09:56,040
All right!

144
00:10:02,180 --> 00:10:05,960
- Yeah! Yeah! - Touchdown Tigers.

145
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:08,460
And the score is now 41-38.

146
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:10,760
Tigers lead with 2. 46 remaining...

147
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:13,000
here at the Buenos Aires Sports Arena.

148
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:14,390
Time out Giants.

149
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:18,100
- Are you all right? - Much better.

150
00:10:18,190 --> 00:10:19,570
- Now. - Good.Yeah!

151
00:10:19,650 --> 00:10:22,230
All right! Way to go, team!

152
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:24,790
Hey! Your helmet.

153
00:10:25,890 --> 00:10:27,920
So, what are you doing after the game?

154
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:32,580
Well, everyone's going to the dance, aren't you?

155
00:10:33,030 --> 00:10:35,690
I don't know. It's my last night as a civilian.

156
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:38,070
- Come on, number 12! Let's go! - Ship out for Tereshkova tomorrow.

157
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:41,620
- You're going to the Fleet Academy? - Uh-huh.

158
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:43,090
That's where I want to go!

159
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:45,800
Come on, number 12! Let's play ball!

160
00:10:45,890 --> 00:10:48,120
Don't get any ideas about my girlfriend!

161
00:10:51,490 --> 00:10:54,240
All is fair in love and war.

162
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:57,770
- Giants! Giants! -Johnny! Yeah!

163
00:11:11,370 --> 00:11:13,000
Hey, yeah!

164
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:16,830
Giants leading 43-41. Just over 22 seconds remaining.

165
00:11:20,670 --> 00:11:22,240
- Yeah! - All right, let's go.

166
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:24,270
Irvin, Lathom, cover the rush.

167
00:11:24,290 --> 00:11:27,200
Perry, fake left. Bertolli, you go long.

168
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:32,010
Rico, flip six, three hole. Got it? Hey, Rico?

169
00:11:32,110 --> 00:11:34,120
- Hey! - What?

170
00:11:34,170 --> 00:11:37,690
You're drifting! Flip six, three hole, on one! Got it?

171
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:41,710
-Just throw me the ball, Diz. - Ready? Break!

172
00:12:01,130 --> 00:12:04,170
Yeah! Go, go, go!

173
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:08,260
All right!

174
00:12:11,430 --> 00:12:13,150
Yeah!

175
00:12:13,770 --> 00:12:16,220
He's in there. It's over.

176
00:12:32,270 --> 00:12:34,920
Who said you could grow up so fast, huh?

177
00:12:34,930 --> 00:12:37,030
Mom, don't get mushy.

178
00:12:38,690 --> 00:12:40,740
This came for you today.

179
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:42,970
I presume, at your request.

180
00:12:46,470 --> 00:12:48,830
A lot of my friends are doing Federal Service.

181
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:51,130
Well, you're not thinking of applying?

182
00:12:51,220 --> 00:12:53,260
Have you lost your mind?

183
00:12:53,350 --> 00:12:56,550
I'd rather take ten lashes in Public Square than see you ruin your life.

184
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:58,890
It's a term of service.

185
00:12:58,980 --> 00:13:00,750
It's not a career.

186
00:13:01,130 --> 00:13:03,100
I just want to get out on my own...

187
00:13:04,650 --> 00:13:07,060
see the galaxy for a couple years.

188
00:13:07,150 --> 00:13:09,840
Johnny, people get killed in the Federal Service.

189
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:13,360
Who gave you this idea? It's that teacher, isn't it?

190
00:13:13,450 --> 00:13:16,700
What's his name? You know the one I'm talking about.

191
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:21,370
- Mr Rasczak. - Rasczak?

192
00:13:22,670 --> 00:13:25,570
Silly name. There should be a law against...

193
00:13:25,590 --> 00:13:27,820
using a school as a recruiting station.

194
00:13:27,870 --> 00:13:31,630
No, Rasczak doesn't do that at all.

195
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:33,880
He sort of discourages you.

196
00:13:33,890 --> 00:13:35,680
Well, that's good.

197
00:13:35,770 --> 00:13:38,520
'Cause you're going to Harvard, and that's the end of it.

198
00:13:38,890 --> 00:13:41,450
It's my decision, not yours.

199
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:44,420
- Oh, is that how it is, huh? - Wait, you two.

200
00:13:44,470 --> 00:13:47,980
Uh, Dad and I have a surprise for you that will settle this.

201
00:13:48,020 --> 00:13:49,910
Can you guess what it is?

202
00:13:50,230 --> 00:13:51,500
No.

203
00:13:52,550 --> 00:13:54,960
You wanted to see the galaxy?

204
00:13:55,740 --> 00:13:58,790
How about a trip to the Outer Rings?

205
00:13:59,060 --> 00:14:01,890
Zegema Beach. Huh?

206
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:06,190
I've always wanted to go there.

207
00:14:06,210 --> 00:14:08,540
Good, good. Then it's all settled.

208
00:14:25,570 --> 00:14:28,650
Sure. Don't go away.

209
00:14:28,660 --> 00:14:30,250
I'm just gonna go see Mr Rasczak.

210
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:34,070
Hey, Rico, do you want to dance?

211
00:14:34,070 --> 00:14:35,930
Actually, Diz, I promised Carmen...

212
00:14:35,950 --> 00:14:38,380
Aw, come on. Too bad for her if she's not around.

213
00:14:41,330 --> 00:14:44,080
You know, it's sad. After tonight, most of us...

214
00:14:44,450 --> 00:14:46,560
probably won't see each other again.

215
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,300
So, you still gonna play for Rio?

216
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:56,390
Yeah, looks like. Unless Tokyo lets me start.

217
00:14:56,930 --> 00:14:59,110
Well, anyone who gets you is lucky.

218
00:15:00,060 --> 00:15:02,730
Johnny, how come we never got together?

219
00:15:06,930 --> 00:15:09,080
Can't we just be friends, Diz?

220
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:12,780
Sure.

221
00:15:16,490 --> 00:15:18,400
- Thank you. - Good night.

222
00:15:18,820 --> 00:15:22,190
Look, Diz, I want to talk to Mr Rasczak.

223
00:15:24,620 --> 00:15:27,030
Well, you better hurry up if you want to catch him.

224
00:15:27,130 --> 00:15:28,460
You're the best.

225
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:43,220
Mr Rasczak!

226
00:15:43,310 --> 00:15:46,260
- What is it, Rico? - I want to thank you.

227
00:15:46,350 --> 00:15:48,930
Your class was the best one I had this year.

228
00:15:49,020 --> 00:15:52,020
Well, it's really not my job to please. I just hope you learned something.

229
00:15:52,110 --> 00:15:53,720
Well, I want to join up.

230
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:55,680
I think I got what it takes to be a citizen.

231
00:15:55,730 --> 00:15:57,900
Good for you. Go find out.

232
00:15:57,940 --> 00:15:59,900
Well, my parents are against it.

233
00:15:59,990 --> 00:16:01,570
And I know it's my choice.

234
00:16:01,660 --> 00:16:03,290
I was wondering...

235
00:16:03,390 --> 00:16:05,380
what would you do if you were me?

236
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,740
Figuring things out for yourself...

237
00:16:07,780 --> 00:16:09,900
is the only freedom anyone really has.

238
00:16:09,950 --> 00:16:11,430
Use that freedom.

239
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:13,490
Make up your own mind, Rico.

240
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:36,910
Don't exaggerate.

241
00:16:36,930 --> 00:16:40,040
I'm serious. I think you have really beautiful eyes.

242
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:42,030
- You know? -Johnny.

243
00:16:44,510 --> 00:16:46,750
Uh, this is Zander.

244
00:16:46,810 --> 00:16:49,460
Yeah, we know each other from the game.

245
00:16:49,540 --> 00:16:54,450
- No hard feelings? - No, none at all. We won.

246
00:16:54,490 --> 00:16:58,300
Come on, Carmen. It's the last dance.

247
00:16:58,330 --> 00:17:00,570
Well, maybe I'll see you at the Academy.

248
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,420
Yeah. Who knows?

249
00:17:03,860 --> 00:17:05,720
Good luck.

250
00:17:06,290 --> 00:17:09,220
Zander's going for pilot too.

251
00:17:10,060 --> 00:17:12,470
You two have so much in common.

252
00:17:12,570 --> 00:17:15,870
Johnny Rico, are you jealous?

253
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:18,410
Well, maybe.

254
00:17:18,490 --> 00:17:20,650
You don't have to be jealous.

255
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,020
Hey, hey, break it up, you two.

256
00:17:27,020 --> 00:17:29,150
There's a place for that sort of thing.

257
00:17:32,170 --> 00:17:35,440
I've been thinking, and I'm gonna do it, Carmen.

258
00:17:36,010 --> 00:17:38,360
I'm gonna go for Federal Service.

259
00:17:38,530 --> 00:17:40,260
That's great.

260
00:17:40,340 --> 00:17:43,570
Carl and I are signing up tomorrow. Come with us.

261
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:44,980
I will.

262
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:53,690
My father's not home tonight.

263
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:18,070
I do now, of my own free will...

264
00:18:18,110 --> 00:18:21,610
after having been duly advised and warned...

265
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:24,910
of the meaning and consequences of this oath...

266
00:18:24,940 --> 00:18:27,290
enrol in the Federal Service...

267
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:29,470
for not less than two years...

268
00:18:29,530 --> 00:18:32,630
and as much longer as may be required...

269
00:18:32,660 --> 00:18:35,230
by the needs of the Federation.

270
00:18:35,770 --> 00:18:38,010
- All set? - Thank you.

271
00:18:42,290 --> 00:18:45,020
Fresh meat for the grinder, eh?

272
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:50,080
- So, how'd you kids do? - I'm gonna be a pilot.

273
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:54,360
Well, good for you. We need all the pilots we can get.

274
00:18:55,730 --> 00:18:58,790
- Hey, did you get starside R and D? - No.

275
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:02,200
- I don't believe it. - I got Games and Theory.

276
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:04,510
Games and Theory?

277
00:19:04,590 --> 00:19:07,240
- That's military intelligence. - Yeah.

278
00:19:07,290 --> 00:19:09,510
Way to go, Carl.

279
00:19:09,550 --> 00:19:12,530
Next time we meet, I'll probably have to salute you.

280
00:19:12,550 --> 00:19:13,960
Hmm.

281
00:19:15,230 --> 00:19:17,140
How about you, son?

282
00:19:17,230 --> 00:19:20,150
- Infantry, sir. - Good for you.

283
00:19:20,170 --> 00:19:22,810
Mobile Infantry made me the man I am today.

284
00:19:24,490 --> 00:19:29,870
All recruits must report to the Federal Transportation Hub within 24 hours.

285
00:19:29,950 --> 00:19:32,570
Welcome to the adventure of Federal Service.

286
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:34,490
Let's make a vow.

287
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:38,490
No matter what, we'll always be friends.

288
00:19:40,210 --> 00:19:41,670
I'll go for that.

289
00:19:43,030 --> 00:19:45,910
Well, chances are we'll never see each other again.

290
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:50,260
We'll be millions of light-years away from each other.

291
00:19:50,350 --> 00:19:52,950
But, uh, yeah, sure. Why not?

292
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:57,300
You'll resign, and that's all there is to it.

293
00:19:57,400 --> 00:20:00,610
It may look bad, but if that's the worst you suffer, then that's fine.

294
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:03,430
- I won't quit! - I'm telling you, you will.

295
00:20:03,520 --> 00:20:05,680
You're not going back. You're going on vacation!

296
00:20:05,700 --> 00:20:07,630
I am not going on vacation!

297
00:20:07,690 --> 00:20:09,320
I want to be a citizen.

298
00:20:09,410 --> 00:20:11,100
It's my decision. I made it.

299
00:20:11,150 --> 00:20:13,270
You walk out that door, you are cut off, young man.

300
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:14,750
You understand me?

301
00:20:14,780 --> 00:20:17,140
All right, that's it! You are cut off!

302
00:20:17,170 --> 00:20:19,610
Johnny, why won't you change your mind?

303
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:21,780
Does citizenship mean that much to you?

304
00:20:22,130 --> 00:20:24,580
Well, yeah, sure.

305
00:20:24,730 --> 00:20:26,420
Well, I hope so.

306
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:29,390
I hope you don't ruin your life over some silly little girl...

307
00:20:29,410 --> 00:20:31,240
who wants to look handsome in a uniform.

308
00:20:31,270 --> 00:20:33,750
- Don't talk about Carmen that way! -Johnny.

309
00:20:33,820 --> 00:20:37,650
Your attention, please. Outbound troops 13-A...

310
00:20:39,810 --> 00:20:41,570
Do you have everything?

311
00:20:41,570 --> 00:20:43,440
Great.

312
00:20:48,740 --> 00:20:50,290
Johnny

313
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:55,340
- You're late. - My dad had to help me pack.

314
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:58,030
Suddenly he's afraid he's never gonna see me again or something.

315
00:20:58,080 --> 00:21:00,650
It was sweet, but it took forever.

316
00:21:00,670 --> 00:21:05,410
Oh. Anyway, I guess I'm ready to go.

317
00:21:05,510 --> 00:21:08,810
Yeah, me too. I'm wearing everything I own.

318
00:21:11,350 --> 00:21:13,260
I'm sorry your parents were mad.

319
00:21:13,860 --> 00:21:16,290
Who cares? The Federation will give me...

320
00:21:16,330 --> 00:21:18,400
everything I need for the next two years, right?

321
00:21:19,660 --> 00:21:23,430
- You talk to Carl? - Yeah, he left this morning.

322
00:21:23,530 --> 00:21:27,540
- Couldn't say where. - Oh, it's exciting, going away.

323
00:21:27,550 --> 00:21:30,330
But I'm scared. Aren't you?

324
00:21:35,140 --> 00:21:37,110
I'm gonna miss you.

325
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:40,480
I'm gonna miss you too.

326
00:21:41,710 --> 00:21:43,560
I love you.

327
00:21:43,730 --> 00:21:46,990
Outbound group 94B to Tereshkova...

328
00:21:47,050 --> 00:21:48,790
That's me.

329
00:21:51,180 --> 00:21:55,130
Just say it once. Try it on for size.

330
00:21:58,650 --> 00:22:00,190
I love you.

331
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:10,690
Don't forget to write.

332
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:12,230
I won't.

333
00:22:27,670 --> 00:22:30,250
Fully automatic Morita. Who wants to hold it?

334
00:22:30,340 --> 00:22:31,710
Me! Me! Me! Me! Me!

335
00:22:31,730 --> 00:22:35,970
Citizen rule. People making a better tomorrow.

336
00:22:44,270 --> 00:22:47,330
A murderer was captured this morning and tried today.

337
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:49,310
Guilty.

338
00:22:50,650 --> 00:22:52,310
Sentence.: death.

339
00:22:52,410 --> 00:22:55,660
Execution tonight at 6.:00. All net. All channels.

340
00:23:03,750 --> 00:23:06,560
If you think you're psychic,

341
00:23:06,750 --> 00:23:08,210
maybe you are.

342
00:23:10,260 --> 00:23:13,480
Federal studies are being conducted in your community.

343
00:23:16,990 --> 00:23:20,680
Every school kid knows that Arachnids are dangerous.

344
00:23:26,380 --> 00:23:29,630
However, Mormon extremists disregarded Federal warnings...

345
00:23:29,650 --> 00:23:33,680
and established Fort Joe Smith deep inside the Arachnid Quarantine Zone.

346
00:23:33,700 --> 00:23:38,260
Too late, they realized that Dantana had already been chosen by other colonists.:

347
00:23:38,380 --> 00:23:39,750
Arachnids.

348
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:51,420
- One, two, three, four! - Most of you will not...

349
00:23:51,450 --> 00:23:53,750
live to be in the Mobile Infantry.

350
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:56,770
The trouble is, you are not good enough the way you are.

351
00:23:56,770 --> 00:23:58,530
Hands at your side!

352
00:23:58,810 --> 00:24:00,180
Chin up.

353
00:24:00,270 --> 00:24:03,550
I am your senior drill instructor, Career Sergeant Zim!

354
00:24:03,590 --> 00:24:07,310
Suck in that gut! Feet together!

355
00:24:08,820 --> 00:24:12,970
To think this had to happen to me. What a bunch of apes.

356
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:13,960
No, strike that!

357
00:24:13,980 --> 00:24:15,340
You don't rate that good.

358
00:24:15,350 --> 00:24:17,560
Never in my life have I seen...

359
00:24:19,910 --> 00:24:22,660
Do you think I'm funny? Do I make you laugh?

360
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:25,020
- Do you think I'm a comedian, son? - I'm sorry.

361
00:24:25,050 --> 00:24:29,270
The first words and the last words out of your stinking holes will be "Sir"!

362
00:24:29,290 --> 00:24:31,630
- Do you get me? - Sir, yes, sir!

363
00:24:31,740 --> 00:24:34,040
You see that armoury? Run around it.

364
00:24:34,070 --> 00:24:36,550
Run, I said! Run, run, run!

365
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:39,080
- Bronski, keep pace! - Move! Move!

366
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:41,040
Now, anytime you think I'm being too tough...

367
00:24:41,050 --> 00:24:43,140
anytime you think I'm being unfair...

368
00:24:43,160 --> 00:24:46,740
anytime you miss your mommy, quit!

369
00:24:46,740 --> 00:24:49,320
You sign form 1240-A, you grab your gear...

370
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:51,900
you take a stroll down Washout Lane!

371
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,850
Do you get me?

372
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:56,090
- Sir, yes, sir! - Pathetic!

373
00:24:56,130 --> 00:24:59,960
I wonder if there's a handful of guts in the whole bunch of you.

374
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:05,240
Now, who here thinks they got what it takes to knock me down?

375
00:25:05,330 --> 00:25:08,540
Sir! I guess maybe I do, sir!

376
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:21,380
Ow! God! God!

377
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:25,860
- You all right, son? - Sir, yes, sir!

378
00:25:25,930 --> 00:25:29,400
It's my arm. I think it's broken, sir.

379
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:31,630
- Medic! - God.

380
00:25:31,980 --> 00:25:34,900
Pain is in your mind!

381
00:25:34,990 --> 00:25:36,940
- Who's next? - Sir!

382
00:25:36,990 --> 00:25:39,820
Recruit Flores reporting for duty, sir!

383
00:25:49,250 --> 00:25:53,150
You specifically requested transfer from Fort Cronkite to this training unit?

384
00:25:53,210 --> 00:25:55,130
Sir, I heard it was the best, sir!

385
00:25:55,140 --> 00:25:56,860
It is the best.

386
00:25:57,920 --> 00:26:00,980
But what makes you think you're good enough?

387
00:26:07,680 --> 00:26:10,300
Now that's the kind of gal who makes squad leader.

388
00:26:10,340 --> 00:26:12,870
That's my job you're talking about.

389
00:26:39,300 --> 00:26:41,660
You know, I'd like to kill that Sergeant Zim.

390
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:44,080
- Whoa, improper attitude! - Watch it.

391
00:26:44,080 --> 00:26:46,070
- They'll kick you out for talking like that. - Bye-bye.

392
00:26:46,100 --> 00:26:48,490
There you go down Washout Lane.

393
00:26:48,510 --> 00:26:51,040
Yup, you either got what it takes, or you don't.

394
00:26:51,050 --> 00:26:53,380
- Hey, there is a line. - Wait your turn, Ace.

395
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:56,740
Hey, at ease, little soldier. It's all the same muck.

396
00:26:56,820 --> 00:26:58,880
Get in line like everyone else.

397
00:27:08,410 --> 00:27:11,170
You got some guts for a rich kid.

398
00:27:11,430 --> 00:27:14,290
I guess you and me could be buddies. What do you say?

399
00:27:15,500 --> 00:27:19,080
- I'm honoured. - Hey! Of course you are.

400
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:21,230
Everybody should have a friend like me.

401
00:27:21,270 --> 00:27:24,270
Come on, Ace. Back of the line now! Back of the line!

402
00:27:25,110 --> 00:27:27,480
- What a jerk, man. - Tough guy.

403
00:27:28,390 --> 00:27:30,470
Hey, Rico, want to sit together?

404
00:27:30,550 --> 00:27:32,050
No thanks, Diz.

405
00:27:34,150 --> 00:27:36,300
What's your malfunction, Rico?

406
00:27:37,420 --> 00:27:38,990
You are.

407
00:27:39,530 --> 00:27:42,790
I joined up to get out on my own, and you had to tag along.

408
00:27:44,490 --> 00:27:47,180
You think I joined the Mobile Infantry because of you?

409
00:27:47,350 --> 00:27:49,300
You saying you didn't?

410
00:27:55,510 --> 00:27:56,880
Hi.

411
00:27:56,930 --> 00:27:59,300
Forget about it, Ace. You don't stand a chance.

412
00:27:59,350 --> 00:28:02,740
What makes you even think you're gonna make squad leader, Rico?

413
00:28:02,750 --> 00:28:04,020
- Something I got, you don't. - Ha!

414
00:28:04,060 --> 00:28:07,260
- You rich kids are all the same. - It isn't about that.

415
00:28:07,270 --> 00:28:09,000
- It's about who's the best. - Hey!

416
00:28:20,280 --> 00:28:21,770
Third squad!

417
00:28:28,610 --> 00:28:31,320
Sir, I don't understand.

418
00:28:31,780 --> 00:28:34,070
Who needs a knife in a nuke fight, anyway?

419
00:28:34,140 --> 00:28:37,720
All you gotta do is push a button, sir.

420
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:39,360
Cease fire.

421
00:28:40,520 --> 00:28:42,850
Put your hand on that wall, trooper.

422
00:28:45,550 --> 00:28:48,320
Put your hand on that wall!

423
00:28:57,710 --> 00:28:58,960
Damn it.

424
00:29:03,950 --> 00:29:08,190
The enemy cannot push a button if you disable his hand.

425
00:29:12,140 --> 00:29:13,430
Medic!

426
00:29:15,870 --> 00:29:18,650
Ah, well, we all have one thing in common.

427
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:21,580
We were all stupid enough to sign up for Mobile Infantry.

428
00:29:21,640 --> 00:29:24,860
- Breckinridge, what's your excuse? - Oh, my family's all farmers.

429
00:29:24,890 --> 00:29:26,830
I hate farming. I mean, uh, Mobile Infantry...

430
00:29:26,860 --> 00:29:28,860
It's like pure picnic by comparison.

431
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:32,050
All right, so they grow 'em big and dumb on the farm planet, huh?

432
00:29:32,140 --> 00:29:34,510
- And pretty! - I like big!

433
00:29:34,600 --> 00:29:38,030
- Djana'D, what about you? - Oh, I'm going in for politics...

434
00:29:38,070 --> 00:29:40,210
and, you know, you gotta be a citizen for that.

435
00:29:40,250 --> 00:29:43,180
- So here I am. - Ah, you want some responsibility.

436
00:29:43,290 --> 00:29:46,530
- Yeah. - Shujimi, come on, let's keep it goin'.

437
00:29:46,570 --> 00:29:49,330
I got into Harvard, but my father says forget it.

438
00:29:49,340 --> 00:29:51,190
It's gonna cost an arm and a leg, you know?

439
00:29:51,210 --> 00:29:52,160
So, if I serve,

440
00:29:52,170 --> 00:29:54,770
Federation pays my way.

441
00:29:54,810 --> 00:29:56,600
I want to have babies.

442
00:29:56,620 --> 00:29:59,520
You know, it's a lot easier to get a licence if you've served.

443
00:29:59,540 --> 00:30:00,700
- So... - I'm going career.

444
00:30:00,710 --> 00:30:03,040
Officer's training. All the way.

445
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:06,160
Future Sky Marshal. All right, Rico, your turn.

446
00:30:08,010 --> 00:30:09,850
Who asked you to be so nosy?

447
00:30:09,900 --> 00:30:12,280
What? I'm the-the bad guy? I'm gonna be a writer, you know?

448
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:14,240
A writer's got a right to be nosy.

449
00:30:14,510 --> 00:30:17,660
Hey, Flores, you know Rico from Buenos Aires.

450
00:30:17,690 --> 00:30:20,560
- What's his story? - Oh, uh,

451
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:23,860
he's here because of a girl.

452
00:30:25,790 --> 00:30:28,200
Oh, Rico! Lover boy!

453
00:30:29,350 --> 00:30:32,670
- He's getting me excited. - He's gonna blow.

454
00:30:36,150 --> 00:30:37,720
Is it you?

455
00:30:41,210 --> 00:30:45,950
This is where we live. It's not much, but it's home.

456
00:30:46,050 --> 00:30:49,710
Right there, that's my bunk, where I dream about you every night.

457
00:30:51,220 --> 00:30:52,800
Boot's pretty tough.

458
00:30:52,890 --> 00:30:55,510
Sometimes I think I won't make it.

459
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:57,890
But then I think about what you're doing, and I try harder.

460
00:30:59,810 --> 00:31:04,780
- Hey, guys! Do you mind? - Try harder, baby, try harder!

461
00:31:08,610 --> 00:31:12,370
Who knows? They might even make me squad leader.

462
00:31:12,740 --> 00:31:15,190
Uh-oh, I better pack it in.

463
00:31:15,320 --> 00:31:18,160
Oh, I love you, baby, I love you!

464
00:31:18,250 --> 00:31:21,910
- Write me! - I love you so much

465
00:31:21,950 --> 00:31:24,840
- I'm gonna kill you guys! - I love you so much

466
00:31:27,550 --> 00:31:29,600
- Bye! Write me. - Bye!

467
00:31:30,580 --> 00:31:32,750
Orbit in five, Ibanez.

468
00:31:32,780 --> 00:31:35,050
First one there gets to fly.

469
00:31:50,360 --> 00:31:52,890
- Locking it down. - Wait! Wait!

470
00:31:54,570 --> 00:31:57,750
Oh, no. Not Ibanez again. She's crazy!

471
00:31:57,760 --> 00:31:59,560
Ready, go!

472
00:32:06,080 --> 00:32:07,410
Yeah!

473
00:32:09,250 --> 00:32:10,930
Deploying wings.

474
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:57,470
How come you're in such a good mood, huh?

475
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,710
'Cause today I get to fly that.

476
00:33:22,620 --> 00:33:25,740
Pilot Trainee Ibanez reporting for duty, ma'am.

477
00:33:25,890 --> 00:33:27,630
Take the number two chair, Ibanez.

478
00:33:27,650 --> 00:33:29,160
- Yes, ma'am. - You see that?

479
00:33:32,630 --> 00:33:38,130
- Identify. - Ibanez, T-3 25-A, clear.

480
00:33:42,890 --> 00:33:45,680
What are you doing here?

481
00:33:46,060 --> 00:33:49,060
I'm the guy whose gonna teach you to fly this crate.

482
00:33:49,570 --> 00:33:52,070
Oh, Assistant Instructor.

483
00:33:52,900 --> 00:33:54,880
Should I call you "sir"?

484
00:33:55,490 --> 00:33:58,960
- Only when I give you an order. - Prepare for departure.

485
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:03,530
It's amazing, us running into each other like this.

486
00:34:03,620 --> 00:34:06,510
- Maybe it's fate. - Maybe not.

487
00:34:06,550 --> 00:34:09,770
Heard about this crazy girl coming through the Academy.

488
00:34:09,780 --> 00:34:14,330
Solid math, a little wild on the stick, but a natural.

489
00:34:14,420 --> 00:34:16,160
And when it turned out to be you,

490
00:34:16,190 --> 00:34:18,420
I just made sure that we would run into each other.

491
00:34:18,440 --> 00:34:21,160
Rodger Young cleared for undocking and departure.

492
00:34:21,170 --> 00:34:22,880
All right, Ibanez.

493
00:34:22,970 --> 00:34:25,340
- Take her out. - Yes, ma'am.

494
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:28,510
All systems go.

495
00:34:52,570 --> 00:34:56,120
In simulation, my supervisors could never keep up.

496
00:34:56,130 --> 00:34:58,520
Well, this isn't simulation any more...

497
00:34:58,550 --> 00:35:00,690
so take her out easy, cadet.

498
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:02,000
Yes, sir.

499
00:35:11,060 --> 00:35:13,450
Five metres from object.

500
00:35:15,770 --> 00:35:17,730
Three metres from object.

501
00:35:21,810 --> 00:35:23,240
Clear.

502
00:35:26,410 --> 00:35:29,660
- Don't exceed port speed. - Or what?

503
00:35:29,690 --> 00:35:34,160
Or they revoke your flight status, and mine.

504
00:35:35,920 --> 00:35:38,290
Your career is in my hands.

505
00:35:45,470 --> 00:35:47,250
Steady as she goes, Number Two.

506
00:35:47,270 --> 00:35:49,280
- Prepare for warp. - Yes, ma'am.

507
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:51,910
Number One, design for Jupiter orbit.

508
00:35:52,600 --> 00:35:56,880
All crew, all sections, stand by to cut in C-drive.

509
00:35:56,890 --> 00:36:00,350
Star drive in five, four...

510
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:02,760
ready, steady...

511
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:04,180
go!

512
00:36:28,230 --> 00:36:30,280
We're going in! Move!

513
00:36:39,190 --> 00:36:41,180
Man, they're defended. No way in.

514
00:36:43,070 --> 00:36:45,440
- Flip six, three hole. - What?

