773
00:55:09,360 --> 00:55:10,600
Hey,Johnny!

774
00:55:12,740 --> 00:55:14,260
Johnny Rico.

775
00:55:16,110 --> 00:55:17,510
Carmen?

776
00:55:20,480 --> 00:55:23,390
Oh. At ease.

777
00:55:23,440 --> 00:55:26,250
Guess I ought to lose the hat when I'm off duty.

778
00:55:26,410 --> 00:55:30,200
- Hi, Diz. - Carmen.

779
00:55:32,490 --> 00:55:34,650
My mother was right about you.

780
00:55:35,200 --> 00:55:37,140
You look great in a uniform.

781
00:55:37,210 --> 00:55:39,110
You look pretty good yourself.

782
00:55:40,920 --> 00:55:42,860
So, what do you hear?

783
00:55:42,920 --> 00:55:45,870
You know about anyone who made it out of BA alive?

784
00:55:45,960 --> 00:55:48,540
Most of the time I don't think about it.

785
00:55:48,630 --> 00:55:50,550
Like it happened to someone else.

786
00:55:50,620 --> 00:55:54,070
Then it hits me, and I, uh, can't stop crying.

787
00:55:54,640 --> 00:55:57,890
Well, we're still alive. Got to be happy about that.

788
00:55:58,310 --> 00:56:01,050
You don't look very happy to see me.

789
00:56:01,850 --> 00:56:03,430
Should I be?

790
00:56:04,020 --> 00:56:05,410
Johnny

791
00:56:06,320 --> 00:56:09,570
It's different now. We're at war.

792
00:56:09,580 --> 00:56:12,980
I mean, I think what I did was probably the best thing for both of us.

793
00:56:13,320 --> 00:56:15,480
Everything copacetic, Lieutenant?

794
00:56:16,490 --> 00:56:18,810
Zander, you remember Johnny.

795
00:56:18,990 --> 00:56:21,310
Zander and I are a flight team now.

796
00:56:21,390 --> 00:56:23,190
Yeah, and we're best in the fleet.

797
00:56:24,300 --> 00:56:25,740
I get it.

798
00:56:26,250 --> 00:56:28,860
This is the part that's best for both of us.

799
00:56:29,170 --> 00:56:32,030
- Don't do me any more favours. - Johnny, wait.

800
00:56:32,040 --> 00:56:34,310
No, forget it, Lieutenant. He's Mobile Infantry.

801
00:56:34,320 --> 00:56:36,370
See, when you're trained to kill...

802
00:56:36,400 --> 00:56:38,480
it just doesn't pay to be polite.

803
00:56:38,680 --> 00:56:41,510
You got something to say about the Mobile Infantry?

804
00:56:41,630 --> 00:56:43,230
I think you heard me.

805
00:56:43,980 --> 00:56:47,120
You want to make something of it, Private?

806
00:56:48,820 --> 00:56:51,090
Not with an officer. No, sir.

807
00:56:51,150 --> 00:56:55,400
- The MI doesn't mint stupid troopers. - Well, let's disregard rank.

808
00:56:55,410 --> 00:56:57,030
Zander, please.

809
00:56:57,320 --> 00:57:01,000
Everybody hear that? Rank is not an issue here.

810
00:57:01,020 --> 00:57:03,950
- Don't do this. - Come on. What's he gonna do?

811
00:57:17,800 --> 00:57:20,340
Come on, jarheads!

812
00:57:20,430 --> 00:57:22,460
Let go of me! Come on! I'm gonna kill you!

813
00:57:23,930 --> 00:57:27,620
I'm gonna kill you! I'll kill you!

814
00:57:27,690 --> 00:57:29,780
Guys! Guys! Quit it! Come on! Come on!

815
00:57:29,820 --> 00:57:32,850
- He's not worth it! - Come on! Come on!

816
00:57:32,940 --> 00:57:37,480
Forget it, Rico! Mobile Infantry and Fleet don't mix. Come on.

817
00:57:38,890 --> 00:57:40,610
Come on, let's go.

818
00:57:42,650 --> 00:57:44,120
Jarheads.

819
00:57:46,580 --> 00:57:49,330
- Mobile Infantry rules! - Yeah!

820
00:57:49,420 --> 00:57:51,750
Oh, God, that hurts.

821
00:57:51,780 --> 00:57:54,760
Hey, well, I got something that might hurt just a little bit more, buddy.

822
00:57:56,260 --> 00:57:59,880
Oh, yeah! We're gonna fight, and we're gonna win!

823
00:58:17,450 --> 00:58:19,390
This is the captain speaking.

824
00:58:19,420 --> 00:58:21,550
All personnel prepare for drop.

825
00:58:21,580 --> 00:58:23,980
We are at D-minus three and counting.

826
00:58:35,460 --> 00:58:38,550
We are going in with first wave.

827
00:58:38,630 --> 00:58:40,760
Means more bugs for us to kill.

828
00:58:40,840 --> 00:58:42,810
You smash the entire area.

829
00:58:42,820 --> 00:58:44,840
You kill anything that has more than two legs.

830
00:58:44,880 --> 00:58:47,190
- You get me? - We get you, sir!

831
00:59:35,150 --> 00:59:37,980
- Plasma, ma'am, from the planet. - Bug batteries.

832
00:59:38,070 --> 00:59:40,980
According to military intelligence, it'll be random and light.

833
00:59:42,570 --> 00:59:45,150
- Drop status? - Drop is...

834
00:59:45,240 --> 00:59:47,320
35 percent complete, ma'am.

835
00:59:52,830 --> 00:59:54,470
Steady as she goes, Number Two.

836
01:00:06,680 --> 01:00:11,430
Remember your training, and you will make it back alive!

837
01:00:29,290 --> 01:00:32,520
This isn't random or light. Someone made a mistake.

838
01:00:32,570 --> 01:00:34,790
That's it. We're empty, ma'am.

839
01:00:44,180 --> 01:00:46,120
Someone made a big goddam mistake!

840
01:00:53,040 --> 01:00:54,890
Break for high orbit!

841
01:01:33,850 --> 01:01:35,620
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

842
01:01:40,320 --> 01:01:41,730
Johnny!

843
01:02:03,380 --> 01:02:06,260
Rockets up!Rocket crew, move up!

844
01:02:30,160 --> 01:02:33,490
- Nuke 'em! Levy! Rico! - Heat 'em up!

845
01:02:37,830 --> 01:02:40,670
- Set. - Fire!

846
01:02:47,380 --> 01:02:49,830
- Follow me! - Let's go!

847
01:02:52,720 --> 01:02:55,760
First platoon, left flank!

848
01:02:55,850 --> 01:02:59,980
Split up! First and second squads, follow me.

849
01:03:00,060 --> 01:03:03,130
Two, cover! One, with me!

850
01:03:03,600 --> 01:03:05,870
Along side! Side to side!

851
01:03:07,400 --> 01:03:08,570
Fire!

852
01:03:26,960 --> 01:03:28,790
Here they come!

853
01:03:32,140 --> 01:03:34,970
- Ace, what are we doing? - Uh, I don't know.

854
01:03:39,940 --> 01:03:44,210
- I don't know. - Kill them! Kill them all!

855
01:03:50,570 --> 01:03:52,400
Come on!

856
01:03:54,530 --> 01:03:57,930
Come on! Come on! You want some?

857
01:03:58,370 --> 01:04:00,510
Here's some! Yeah!

858
01:04:00,540 --> 01:04:02,380
Here's some of this!

859
01:04:05,380 --> 01:04:07,450
Oh, my God!

860
01:04:07,550 --> 01:04:09,440
Shujimi!

861
01:04:10,050 --> 01:04:12,090
No, no, no!

862
01:04:14,510 --> 01:04:16,660
Help! Help! Help!

863
01:04:18,520 --> 01:04:21,070
No! God!

864
01:04:26,190 --> 01:04:27,940
Let's get out of here!

865
01:04:30,950 --> 01:04:32,770
Fall back!

866
01:04:59,720 --> 01:05:02,000
All units,What's going on? fall back to retrieval.

867
01:05:02,030 --> 01:05:04,010
Repeat.You got com? All units...

868
01:05:04,020 --> 01:05:05,550
fall back to retrieval.It's a general retreat!

869
01:05:05,580 --> 01:05:07,400
- Back to the boats! - Come on!

870
01:05:07,420 --> 01:05:09,480
Come on, let's go!

871
01:05:09,490 --> 01:05:12,410
We've just landed here on what cap troopers...

872
01:05:12,410 --> 01:05:14,810
are calling Big K...

873
01:05:14,820 --> 01:05:17,200
with the 6th Mobile Infantry Division.

874
01:05:17,220 --> 01:05:20,240
It's an ugly planet, a bug planet.

875
01:05:20,240 --> 01:05:22,940
A planet hostile to life as we...

876
01:05:27,840 --> 01:05:29,330
Help me!

877
01:05:33,510 --> 01:05:34,910
Squad right!

878
01:05:46,850 --> 01:05:49,610
Come on! Go, go, go!

879
01:05:49,690 --> 01:05:51,660
Get out of here now!

880
01:05:52,950 --> 01:05:55,100
- Watch your step! - Watch your flank! Watch your flank!

881
01:05:55,200 --> 01:05:57,180
GXR, we're being overrun.

882
01:06:06,960 --> 01:06:09,120
Kitten, no!

883
01:06:40,320 --> 01:06:41,820
Oh, God!

884
01:06:41,830 --> 01:06:45,910
Oh, God! Oh! Oh!

885
01:07:15,190 --> 01:07:17,140
Crisis for humankind.

886
01:07:17,280 --> 01:07:19,240
Fleet officials admit they underestimated...

887
01:07:19,270 --> 01:07:22,370
the Arachnids' defensive capability.

888
01:07:22,870 --> 01:07:25,650
Accepting responsibility for Klendathu...

889
01:07:25,680 --> 01:07:27,990
Sky Marshal Dienes resigns.

890
01:07:28,210 --> 01:07:31,010
His successor, Sky Marshal Tahat Meru...

891
01:07:31,060 --> 01:07:33,450
outlines her new strategy.

892
01:07:33,540 --> 01:07:35,450
To fight the bug...

893
01:07:35,550 --> 01:07:38,320
we must understand the bug.

894
01:07:38,410 --> 01:07:41,600
We can ill afford another Klendathu.

895
01:07:43,680 --> 01:07:46,020
Federal scientists struggle to explain...

896
01:07:46,030 --> 01:07:48,680
the intelligent military actions of the Arachnids.

897
01:07:48,770 --> 01:07:51,120
When a colony reaches a certain size...

898
01:07:51,160 --> 01:07:53,770
300 generations or something, it gets smarter.

899
01:07:53,790 --> 01:07:55,550
- Insects with intelligence? - Now, wait...

900
01:07:55,550 --> 01:07:57,190
Have you ever met one? I can't believe...

901
01:07:57,190 --> 01:08:00,360
- I am hearing this nonsense. - Would you just wait a moment?

902
01:08:00,360 --> 01:08:02,260
- This is the most ridiculous conversation I have ever had. - Maybe... Maybe...

903
01:08:02,270 --> 01:08:06,030
there is some kind of bug that we haven't seen yet.:

904
01:08:06,060 --> 01:08:08,640
a leadership caste, a-a hive brain.

905
01:08:08,670 --> 01:08:13,320
Brain Bugs? Frankly, I find the idea of a bug that thinks offensive!

906
01:08:27,060 --> 01:08:31,050
Ticonderoga, this is Rodger Young requesting approach vector.

907
01:08:31,090 --> 01:08:33,020
Affirmative, Rodger Young.

908
01:08:33,030 --> 01:08:36,070
One-zero-zero-niner-five-two.

909
01:08:36,070 --> 01:08:37,650
Welcome back.

910
01:08:39,070 --> 01:08:40,400
My God.

911
01:08:42,320 --> 01:08:44,400
How could this happen?

912
01:08:44,490 --> 01:08:47,080
We thought we were smarter than the bugs.

913
01:09:26,030 --> 01:09:28,720
It's strange. There's almost no wounded at all.

914
01:09:28,760 --> 01:09:30,950
Bugs don't take prisoners.

915
01:09:39,840 --> 01:09:41,290
Oh, no.

916
01:09:42,670 --> 01:09:43,920
Look.

917
01:09:48,510 --> 01:09:50,800
- Carmen... - See it? Right there.

918
01:10:12,630 --> 01:10:15,390
- There he is. - Come on, we'll just wake him up.

919
01:10:15,470 --> 01:10:19,880
Hey,Johnny! Hey!

920
01:10:19,970 --> 01:10:22,890
- Hey, Rico! - Hey,Johnny!

921
01:10:22,980 --> 01:10:24,890
- Hey, Rico!Wake up! - How you doin', fish boy?

922
01:10:24,980 --> 01:10:27,550
Hey, look. You're dead!

923
01:10:27,650 --> 01:10:29,940
Killed in action!

924
01:10:32,320 --> 01:10:34,230
- Three more days. - Three days.

925
01:10:34,320 --> 01:10:36,310
- And you're out. - Good as new. See you later.

926
01:10:36,410 --> 01:10:37,740
Bye.

927
01:11:06,940 --> 01:11:08,680
So what do you hear about our new unit?

928
01:11:08,770 --> 01:11:11,180
Roughnecks killed more bugs than any other outfit on Big K.

929
01:11:11,280 --> 01:11:14,110
Yeah, well, I hear their lieutenant's a real nutbuster.

930
01:11:17,120 --> 01:11:18,780
Who's top kick?

931
01:11:21,290 --> 01:11:22,950
You want the job, huh?

932
01:11:23,040 --> 01:11:24,370
I wouldn't mind.

933
01:11:24,460 --> 01:11:26,330
I would.

934
01:11:27,790 --> 01:11:29,120
Just doing my part.

935
01:11:29,210 --> 01:11:30,670
Orders.

936
01:11:33,300 --> 01:11:34,710
Yours?

937
01:11:34,800 --> 01:11:36,540
Where you been besides Big K?

938
01:11:36,630 --> 01:11:40,500
- Outer rings, Zegema Beach. - Zegema Beach?

939
01:11:40,600 --> 01:11:42,970
- I always wanted to go there. - Good luck.

940
01:11:43,060 --> 01:11:48,130
- It's not there any more. - So, I hear your lieutenant's a real nutbuster.

941
01:11:51,230 --> 01:11:53,980
No one talks about the lieutenant that way.

942
01:11:54,070 --> 01:11:56,520
- He saved my life. - Mine too.

943
01:11:57,910 --> 01:11:59,780
- Same for me. - Me too.

944
01:12:01,580 --> 01:12:04,490
Well, sounds like he's quite a guy.

945
01:12:04,580 --> 01:12:06,240
Who do you think saved your ass?

946
01:12:07,420 --> 01:12:10,870
Stand by. Attention on deck!

947
01:12:23,260 --> 01:12:25,340
This is for you new people.

948
01:12:25,430 --> 01:12:27,470
I only have one rule:

949
01:12:27,560 --> 01:12:30,930
Everyone fights. No one quits.

950
01:12:31,020 --> 01:12:34,020
You don't do your job, I'll shoot you.

951
01:12:34,110 --> 01:12:35,350
Do you get me?

952
01:12:35,440 --> 01:12:37,440
We get you, sir!

953
01:12:39,160 --> 01:12:41,560
- Welcome to the Roughnecks. - Rasczak's Roughnecks!

954
01:12:42,830 --> 01:12:44,900
At ease. Listen up.

955
01:12:44,990 --> 01:12:48,580
We got a new Sky Marshal and a new battle plan.

956
01:12:48,670 --> 01:12:51,070
We're gonna clean out the systems outlying Klendathu...

957
01:12:51,170 --> 01:12:53,330
one planet at a time.

958
01:12:53,420 --> 01:12:55,580
Tomorrow we hit Tango Urilla.

959
01:12:55,670 --> 01:13:00,080
After Fleet glasses the planet, MI mops up.

960
01:13:00,180 --> 01:13:01,420
Carry on.

961
01:13:51,690 --> 01:13:54,260
All right. Spread out!

962
01:13:54,360 --> 01:13:58,020
Fire teams! You locate a bug hole, nuke it.

963
01:14:05,870 --> 01:14:07,780
Watkins, shake out Flores and Rico.

964
01:14:07,870 --> 01:14:10,190
Copy that. Move out!

965
01:14:10,290 --> 01:14:13,120
First platoon, we're going for that ridge.

966
01:14:13,210 --> 01:14:16,130
- Levy, you're with me. - No, I'm in A Squad. I'm going with Rico.

967
01:14:16,210 --> 01:14:17,710
Shut up and follow me!

968
01:14:56,130 --> 01:14:57,950
Hey, you like that?

969
01:14:58,040 --> 01:15:00,040
Fungus-sucking sack of maggot puke!

970
01:15:00,130 --> 01:15:01,710
It's dead, Watkins! It's dead!

971
01:15:06,840 --> 01:15:09,090
Ain't much to look at after you scrape them off your boot.

972
01:15:10,640 --> 01:15:13,390
Bug hole. There.

973
01:15:28,160 --> 01:15:29,320
Nuke 'em, Rico!

974
01:15:35,330 --> 01:15:36,790
Fire in the hole!

975
01:15:48,510 --> 01:15:50,920
Watkins, we're under heavy attack. Position M-4.

976
01:15:51,010 --> 01:15:53,260
- Get over here! - Move!

977
01:16:03,360 --> 01:16:06,360
- You got a bug problem, ma'am? - Ah, stow it, trooper!

978
01:16:27,930 --> 01:16:30,000
Tanker!

979
01:16:30,090 --> 01:16:33,180
- Oh, shit! - Come on! Move!

980
01:16:41,900 --> 01:16:43,810
Get down!

981
01:16:51,950 --> 01:16:53,150
Come on!

982
01:18:01,480 --> 01:18:03,550
Stay down, sucker!

983
01:18:05,650 --> 01:18:07,230
Call for retrieval.

984
01:18:07,320 --> 01:18:10,400
- Medic! - Nice moves.

985
01:18:10,490 --> 01:18:12,730
Where'd you learn how to do that, soldier?

986
01:18:12,820 --> 01:18:15,910
Back in school, sir. Don't you remember?

987
01:18:15,990 --> 01:18:19,990
- I was captain of the team. - Rico?

988
01:18:20,080 --> 01:18:22,830
- Sir. - I need a corporal.

989
01:18:22,920 --> 01:18:26,500
You're it until you're dead or till I find somebody better.

990
01:18:27,420 --> 01:18:29,410
Thank you, sir.

991
01:18:29,510 --> 01:18:32,180
- All right, saddle up! Show's over. - Way to go, Corporal.

992
01:18:32,260 --> 01:18:37,600
- Hey, I need a squad leader. - Oh, no. No, I've been there and blew it.

993
01:18:37,680 --> 01:18:39,090
I'm just here to fight.

994
01:18:40,390 --> 01:18:42,550
What about it, Diz?

995
01:18:42,640 --> 01:18:46,600
First sergeant, get your gear in section...Looks like I'm your girl, sir.

996
01:18:51,530 --> 01:18:53,150
- Catch you later. - All right.

997
01:18:59,160 --> 01:19:01,030
Listen up!

998
01:19:01,120 --> 01:19:04,320
I expect the best, and I give the best!

999
01:19:08,170 --> 01:19:09,500
Here's the beer!

1000
01:19:13,550 --> 01:19:15,510
Here's the entertainment!

1001
01:19:20,010 --> 01:19:22,010
Have fun! That's an order!

1002
01:19:23,100 --> 01:19:24,680
This one's for me!

1003
01:19:26,100 --> 01:19:27,680
Thank you, Lieutenant!

1004
01:19:31,400 --> 01:19:32,730
Rico!

1005
01:19:34,200 --> 01:19:36,270
You kill bugs good.

1006
01:19:36,360 --> 01:19:37,690
Thanks.

1007
01:19:39,530 --> 01:19:41,860
You knew the lieutenant before the war.

1008
01:19:41,950 --> 01:19:43,860
What was he like?

1009
01:19:43,960 --> 01:19:47,040
He was a teacher. Kind of like he knew it all.

1010
01:19:47,130 --> 01:19:49,200
He always had this little smile.

1011
01:19:49,290 --> 01:19:52,710
Yeah, well, he don't smile much any more.

1012
01:19:52,800 --> 01:19:56,550
Yeah, well, I guess your bottle fills up real quick when your kids get smeared.

1013
01:19:56,630 --> 01:19:59,090
- Come on, Corporal. - Ah, nah, I don't do that any more.

1014
01:19:59,180 --> 01:20:01,670
I remember when you used to dance. Come on.

1015
01:20:01,760 --> 01:20:03,180
Do I have to pull rank?

1016
01:20:05,980 --> 01:20:07,520
Excuse me, sir.

1017
01:20:16,320 --> 01:20:21,400
Rico. You once asked me for advice. Want some now?

1018
01:20:21,490 --> 01:20:24,200
- Yes, sir. - Lieutenant, HQ is on the com.

1019
01:20:26,660 --> 01:20:28,700
Never pass up a good thing.

1020
01:20:37,680 --> 01:20:40,300
Watkins. Beer?

1021
01:21:02,830 --> 01:21:05,400
So, Rico, what are you doing after the dance?

1022
01:21:53,040 --> 01:21:54,420
What's so funny?

1023
01:21:55,960 --> 01:21:58,120
You know, just the way things work out.

1024
01:22:15,650 --> 01:22:18,140
We finally got together, Diz.

1025
01:22:21,320 --> 01:22:22,820
I love you,Johnny.

1026
01:22:33,420 --> 01:22:34,660
Rico!

1027
01:22:37,420 --> 01:22:40,260
We're moving out. There's been a distress call from General Owen on Planet P.

1028
01:22:40,340 --> 01:22:42,500
So get your shit wired and report in ten minutes.

1029
01:22:42,590 --> 01:22:44,000
Yes, sir.

1030
01:22:44,090 --> 01:22:45,590
Who's that with you?

1031
01:22:49,180 --> 01:22:51,260
Flores, sir.

1032
01:22:52,440 --> 01:22:54,510
Make it 20 minutes.

